Job Description:
Position Objective
HR & Admin Supervisor is responsible for leading the HR & Admin Officer, overseeing activities of professional HR & Admin in term of monitoring the work performance. This position is to define and communicate the business’s KPIs and targets to the team member on a regular basis, analyse patterns of working behavior, and subsequently define data-driven action strategies in order to consistently optimize the business’s commercial performance.

The recruitment:
• To work closely with Head of Department for manpower planning;
• To double check with Head of Department for the updated Job Description with clear main responsibilities and job requirement;
• To build good relationship with target school, Universities and Training Center who can provide the young and good talents candidates;
• To ensure the recruitment on time with the right candidate.
The compliance documents:
• To collect the compliance documents before the starting date of new employee as per the current practice;
• To prepare and conduct the orientation for new employee with the warm welcome;
• To keep good record the document into the personal file/ HRMS.

The probation evaluation:
• To support and alert the probation evaluation to head of department at least one week in advance before end of probation period;
• To follow up with head of department for the result of probation evaluation;
• To setup the appointment with new employee who passed/failed the probation at least 3 days before end of probation period;
The employee engagement:
• To keep good relationship with employee and work with line manager/ head of department for the feedback for the team member about their comments and feedback;
• To provide the feedback with good solutions to the employee on time in order to maintain the staff motivation;
• To always keep staff’s motivation and build the positive mindset to the employee for the purpose of good performance and career development growth; 
• To work with head of department for the employee career planning/ successor planning.

The compensation & benefits:
• To support line manager for database of payroll calculations to ensure the monthly salary paid on time;
• To monitor and explain to the employee for any questions related to the compensations calculation;
• To ensure the headcount and employee status updated in term of employee in and out and others;
• To declare the monthly NSSF (National Social Security Fund) to MoLVT.

The performance management:
• To work with head of department for setting up the employee performance (objectives during and after probation);
• To provide the guideline and orientation to head of department on how to conduct and lead the performance evaluation;
• To keep remind to head of department for preparing and conducting the performance evaluations to team member and submit to HR department on time.
The weekly Report:
• To ensure the weekly report is on time as per deadline;
• To assist the management meeting as the minute taker;
• Others work assigned by line manager.

The leadership:
• To support the HR & Admin Officer in term of improving the work performance;
• To keep motivate the HR & Admin Officer and ensure the career development growth.

Job Requirement:
• Bachelor's Degree in HR Management or equivalent;
• Have at least 4 years of experience as HR & Admin leader and have the experience within automotive industry is a plus;
• Have good knowledge of labor law, recruitment, staff engagement, compensation and compliance;
• Be able to speak English and Chinese is an advantage; 
• Have good communication skills and be able to involve with problem solving; 
• Have at least good in Microsoft Office;
